transcript.text: Hello and welcome to on Print Shop.
In this video we will learn about new upload features in Storefront in version 8.0.
Here are the key features to upload multiple artwork files.
We have improved the overall multiple file upload feature for the front side using the Add More button.
Your customer can now upload multiple files as well as multiple jobs for a product.
For all the extra pages your customers upload, you can set a mask image for them.
For the file uploader extra fields, customers can now upload multiple files using a single file uploader button.
This can be implemented by a simple setting.
Let's check the features in admin.
Go to Settings Upload tab.
There are two buttons.
First is Allow Multiple Job which is an existing product setting for the provision to allow add multiple jobs renamed here.
2nd we have Allow multiple file upload which is product level setting allow to upload multiple files in a single job.
Enable it and save here.

When we go to storefront and click on upload design, here we can see Add more Files button which will allow customers to upload multiple files in a single job with default page name file one which can be changed by customer while uploading the file.
Also customer can upload multiple jobs by clicking on Add more jobs button.
Next feature is for the products with mask images.
When we go to mask image section Add new, we have given the provision to upload mask images for the extra pages.
This mask will be applied to all extra pages uploaded.
Another feature is in the additional option, click on Add New.
Here we have given Upload Multiple Files option which will allow customers to upload multiple files using a single file uploader.
When we go to storefront, click on Select File.
There we can upload multiple files at once.
In case of any further queries, feel free to contact us via chat or e-mail.
Thank you for your time to watch this video.
Have a wonderful day.

Upload mask image for template, it allows you to draw on particular area of image which is transparent and rest of the portion will be as it is. E.g. T-Shirt, CD covers, Photo frames where you want you can make designs on
some particular portion of the image.
Note :- Upload .gif, .png or .pdf file only. Image of same file type needs to be uploaded for both Portrait and Landscape orientation.
Mask images can be uploaded separately for different scenarios:
Use left side options Upload Landscape File and Upload Portrait File to upload mask image for use in designer studio canvas only.
Use right side options Upload PrintReady Landscape File and Upload PrintReady Portrait File to upload mask image for use in print ready files and PDF preview only.
